• Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG – A group of Eastern Cape land owners have headed to the Constitutional Court to get their land back. Earlier this year the landowners' hopes were dashed when the Supreme Court of Appeal handed down judgment and dismissed their appeal against an order of Land Claims Court for restitution of rights for a portion of land petitioners known as the Salem community. WATCH: Malema calls for land to be shared Salem was founded in 1820 when British settlers arrived there. In 2014, the Land Claims Court ruled the Salem Community had a right in the land of the old Salem commonage. eNCA